Dyndns client tool: ruby scripts run on your linux pc to update your ip for your hostname in DynDns system.

Run setup.sh to create /usr/local/dyndns_client folder and copy in-need files to the new folder
Go to the /usr/local/dyndns_client, edit the dynclient.rb file, replace the information about hostname, username and password of your DynDns account.

You could run directly dynclient.sh, or create cron schedule job to run this tool.
